mibatmIntfSigParamsTable.name: mibatmIntfSigParamsTable
mibatmIntfSigParamsTable.description: A list of mibatmIntfSigParams profile entries.

mibatmIntfSigParamsEntry.name: mibatmIntfSigParamsEntry
mibatmIntfSigParamsEntry.description: A mibatmIntfSigParams entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibatmIntfSigParams profile.

atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress.name: atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress_Shelf
atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress.description: The number of the shelf that the addressed physical device resides on.

atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress.name: atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress_Slot
atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress.description: The number of the slot that the addressed physical device resides on.

atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress.name: atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress_ItemNumber
atmIntfSigParams_Address_PhysicalAddress.description: A number that specifies an addressable entity within the context of shelf and slot.

atmIntfSigParams_Address_LogicalItem.name: atmIntfSigParams_Address_LogicalItem
atmIntfSigParams_Address_LogicalItem.description: A number that specifies an addressable logical entity within the context of a physical address.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_MaxRestart.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_MaxRestart
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_MaxRestart.description: Maximum number of unacknowledged tx RESTART.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_MaxStatenq.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_MaxStatenq
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_MaxStatenq.description: Maximum number of unacknowledged tx STATUS ENQ.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T301Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T301Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T301Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for alerting supervision function. This timer is started on receipt of ALERT in Call received/delivered state and stopped when CONNECT is received.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T303Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T303Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T303Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after SETUP is sent. This timer is stopped when the CONNECT, CALL PROCEEDING, or RELEASE COMPLETE is received.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T306Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T306Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T306Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for a RELEASE_COMPLETE to be received after a release has been sent.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T308Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T308Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T308Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after RELEASE is sent. This is a release indication timer. This timer is started when the RELEASE message is sent and normally is stopped when the RELEASE or RELEASE COMPLETE is received.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T309Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T309Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T309Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for Q.SAAL to reconnect. After this time, calls are dropped. When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T310Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T310Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T310Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after SETUP is received. Also called the CALL PROCEEDING timer.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T313Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T313Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T313Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after CONNECT is sent. Also called the connect request timer. It is started when the CONNECT is sent and stopped when the CONNECT ACKNOWLEDGE is recieved.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T316Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T316Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T316Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after RESTART is sent. Also called the restart request timer. It is started when the RESTART is sent and stopped when the RESTART ACKNOWLEDGE is recieved.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T317Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T317Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T317Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references. This timer is started as a result of a restart and cleared when all the internal call references are cleared. Should be less than the the likely value of T316 of the peer.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T322Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T322Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T322Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for a response after STATUS ENQ is sent.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T331Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T331Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T331Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T333Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T333Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T333Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T397Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T397Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T397Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for internal clearing of call references.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T398Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T398Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T398Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for receipt of a response to a DROP PARTY that was sent.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T399Ms.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T399Ms
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T399Ms.description: Timer (in msec) for receipt of a response to an ADD PARTY that was sent.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_SaalRetryM.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_SaalRetryMs
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_SaalRetryM.description: Timer value for retrying AAL_ESTABLISH messages.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T303NumRet.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T303NumReties
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T303NumRet.description: Number of times SETUP could be resent in case of T303 timer expiry.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T308NumRet.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T308NumRetries
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T308NumRet.description: Number of times RELEASE could be sent in case of T308 timer expiry.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T316NumRet.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T316NumRetries
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T316NumRet.description: Number of times RESTART could be sent in case RESTART ACK is not received withinn T316 timer expiry.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T322NumRet.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T322NumRetries
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_T322NumRet.description: Number of times STAT ENQ could be sent before a response is received within the T322 timer expiry.

atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_AssignVpiV.name: atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_AssignVpiVci
atmIntfSigParams_Q2931Options_AssignVpiV.description: In the case of UNI4.0 and PNNI this parameter specifies who assigns the VPI/VCI. TRUE will allow the local stack and FALSE will let the partner stack to assign.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_MaxCc.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_MaxCc
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_MaxCc.description: Maximum number of control PDU (BGN, END, RESYNC) retransmissions.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_MaxPd.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_MaxPd
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_MaxPd.description: Maximum number of Sequenced data PDU's between poll.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TccMs.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TccMs
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TccMs.description: Retry time (in msec) for control PDU's(BGN, END, RESYNC).

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TpollMs.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TpollMs
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TpollMs.description: Poll sent (in msec) when active. When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_Tkeepalive.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TkeepaliveMs
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_Tkeepalive.description: Poll sent (in msec) when in transient state. When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_Tnorespons.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TnoresponseMs
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_Tnorespons.description: STAT received at least this period(in msec). When set to 0, a default value based on an ATM signaling protocol will be used.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TidleMs.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TidleMs
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_TidleMs.description: Poll sent (in msec) when idle -- UNI 3.1, only.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_PollAfterR.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_PollAfterRetransmission
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_PollAfterR.description: Specifies after retransmitting PDUs whether a POLL must be sent before sending any further PDUs.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_RepeatUsta.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_RepeatUstat
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_RepeatUsta.description: Specifies whether two USTAT messages should be sent each time it is required to be sent.

atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_UstatRspTo.name: atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_UstatRspToPoll
atmIntfSigParams_QsaalOptions_UstatRspTo.description: Specifies whether a USTAT should be sent in response to a POLL indicating an out of sequence PDU.
